{"id":11298,"date":"2013-01-09T20:28:19","date_gmt":"2013-01-10T01:28:19","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=11298"},"modified":"2021-08-16T14:05:05","modified_gmt":"2021-08-16T10:05:05","slug":"hikmah-gradual-revelation-quran","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/09\/hikmah-gradual-revelation-quran\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Wahy: Wisdom in gradual revelation of Quran"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Yusuf ibn Mahak reported: Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, said, &#8220;Verily, the first verses to be revealed were from the shorter chapters at the end of the Quran. In them is mentioned Paradise and Hellfire, until people were firmly established upon Islam and verses of lawful and unlawful were revealed. If the first verse to be revealed was &#8216;do not drink wine,&#8217; they would have said, &#8216;we will never stop drinking wine.&#8217; And if the first verse to be revealed was &#8216;do not commit adultery,&#8217; they would have said, &#8216;we will never stop committing adultery.'&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4993<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/em>(authentic) according to Al-Bukhari<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u0646 \u064a\u064f\u0648\u0633\u064f\u0641\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0647\u064e\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u0632\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0651\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u0632\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0633\u064f\u0648\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064c \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0641\u064e\u0